        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "After authenticating, the ClientLogin class creates a new Zend_Http_Client object--- ignoring previously set proxy adapter settings.  This makes the authentication request succeed in going through the proxy, but all other requests with the client returned from the ClientLogin code will fail, as they won't be going through the proxy.\n\nSee:\nZend_Gdata_ClientLogin::getHttpClient (line 132 -- $client = new Zend_Http_Client).\n"
        },
